cs.DB, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.CY 

This paper discusses the design and evaluation of protected search systems for databases, which falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the security aspects of these systems, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The evaluation of the current state of protected search systems and the analysis of attacks against them involve algorithms and data structures, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the tradeoffs between security, functionality, performance, and usability, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) and cyber security (cs.CY).
